    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to your instruction 223 and my dispatch No. 316, missionary troubles
                    still spreading. The situation very critical. The ministers of England, France,
                    Germany, Italy, and the United States to-day sent foreign office second
                    identical note demanding publication of strong imperial decree without delay. If
                    Chinese Government absolutely refuse and the situation does not materially
                    improve, I advise naval demonstration by war vessels of each Government should
                    be made in North China waters. My colleagues have telegraphed their Government
                    similarly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
